  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Chalet Hôtel le Prieuré &amp; Spa is situated in the heart of <a data-udi="umb://document/6d1f6b40d62d48a6acbcf99f87501ea0" href="/{localLink:umb://document/6d1f6b40d62d48a6acbcf99f87501ea0}" title="Chamonix">Chamonix</a> and recently refurbished, it provides the ideal base for exploring the fantastic skiing around the Chamonix valley. The cosy atmosphere Hotel Prieuré creates helps to unwind after an energetic day on the slopes. The bedrooms are all decorated in a lovely contemporary wooden chalet style - with this theme continuing throughout the hotel - and will provide you with unforgettable views of the Mont Blanc or Aiguilles de Chamonix.</p>
<h2>Great location</h2>
<p>Staying at the Chalet Hôtel le Prieuré &amp; Spa provides prime location, you'll be just a minutes' walk from Chamonix centre filled with restaurants, cafes and a variety of shops. The hotel is also a short walk from the Brevent lift and there is bus stop 100 metres away providing free buses taking you to other ski lifts across Chamonix.  </p>
<h2>Restaurant and bar </h2>
<p>Prepare for the slopes and enjoy your breakfast in '<span>Le Rôtissier', Prieuré's restaurant </span>overlooking the Mont Blanc massif. After an exhilarating day in the snow, take off your boots, warm up by the fire and browse the cocktail menu in the hotel's cosy piano bar. The bar will also welcome you for a sweet or savoury snack during the day and there is also musical events throughout the season. There's also an amazing opportunity to dine around at the sister hotel, Hotel Lykke, or Brasserie I'M, that's located right in the middle of <a data-udi="umb://document/6d1f6b40d62d48a6acbcf99f87501ea0" href="/{localLink:umb://document/6d1f6b40d62d48a6acbcf99f87501ea0}" title="Chamonix">Chamonix</a> resort centre, both are included in the half board offering.</p>
<h2>Soothing spa and relaxation</h2>
<p>Recently added, the spa and f<span>itness area is the perfect place to relax and rejuvenate after a day on the slopes. Soothe your muscles in the hammam and sauna, or soak away the aches and pains in the jacuzzi. Make the most of the heated indoor pool which is the perfect place to unwind after a day of exploring Chamonix. Treat yourself to a Cinq Mondes treatment or massage to fully unwind, then head to the rest room where you can marvel at the incredible views over Mont Blanc. It is recommended that you book your treatments on arrival as they are incredibly popular. </span></p>]]></description>
